"$ sudo ifdown eth0=pppoe\n"
"..."
msgstr ""
"$ sudo ifdown eth0=pppoe\n"
"..."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12834
msgid "The interface <literal>eth0</literal> is down and disconnected, again."
msgstr "L'interface <literal>eth0</literal> est de nouveau dsactive et dconnecte."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12835
msgid "Let's move your PC to a location without LAN or BB-modem but with POTS and modem.  You bring up the <emphasis role=\"strong\">network interface</emphasis> <literal>ppp0</literal> by assigning the <emphasis role=\"strong\">network configuration</emphasis> name <literal>pots</literal> to it by the following."
msgstr "Dplaons votre PC  un emplacement sans rseau local et sans modem large bande mais avec un POTS et un modem (modem sur le rseau commut). Vous activez l'<emphasis role=\"strong\">interface rseau</emphasis> <literal>ppp0</literal> en lui assignant le nom de <emphasis role=\"strong\">configuration rseau</emphasis> <literal>pots</literal> de la manire suivante&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12836
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ sudo ifup ppp0=pots\n"
"..."
msgstr ""
"$ sudo ifup ppp0=pots\n"
"..."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12838
msgid "The interface <literal>ppp0</literal> is up and connected to the Internet with PPP."
msgstr "L'interface <literal>ppp0</literal> est active et connecte  Internet par PPP."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12839
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ sudo ifdown ppp0=pots\n"
"..."
msgstr ""
"$ sudo ifdown ppp0=pots\n"
"..."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12841
msgid "The interface <literal>ppp0</literal> is down and disconnected from the Internet."
msgstr "L'interface <literal>ppp0</literal> est inactive est dconnecte d'Internet."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12842
msgid "You should check the \"<literal>/etc/network/run/ifstate</literal>\" file for the current network configuration state of the <literal>ifupdown</literal> system."
msgstr "Vous devriez vrifier l'tat actuel de la configuration du rseau du systme <literal>ifupdown</literal> dans le fichier &nbsp;<literal>/etc/network/run/ifstate</literal>&nbsp;."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><warning><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12844
msgid "You may need to adjust numbers at the end of <literal>eth*</literal>, <literal>ppp*</literal>, etc. if you have multiple network interfaces."
msgstr "Il se peut que vous ayez besoin d'ajuster le nombre  la fin de <literal>eth*</literal>, <literal>ppp*</literal>, etc. si vous avez plusieurs interfaces rseau."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12848
msgid "Scripting with the ifupdown system"
msgstr "Scripts avec le systme ifupdown"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12849
msgid "The <literal>ifupdown</literal> system automatically runs scripts installed in \"<literal>/etc/network/*/</literal>\" while exporting environment variables to scripts."
msgstr "Le systme <literal>ifupdown</literal> lance automatiquement les scripts qui sont installs dans &nbsp;<literal>/etc/network/*/</literal>&nbsp; en exportant les variables d'environnement vers les scripts."

