msgstr "&lt;famille_d_adresses&gt; de l'interface"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12892
msgid "\"<literal>$METHOD</literal>\""
msgstr "&nbsp;<literal>$METHOD</literal>&nbsp;"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12895
msgid "&lt;method_name&gt; of the interface. (e.g., \"static\")"
msgstr "&lt;nom_mthode&gt; de l'interface. (par exemple &nbsp;static&nbsp;)"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12900
msgid "\"<literal>$MODE</literal>\""
msgstr "&nbsp;<literal>$MODE</literal>&nbsp;"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12903
msgid "\"start\" if run from <literal>ifup</literal>, \"stop\" if run from <literal>ifdown</literal>"
msgstr "&nbsp;&nbsp; si lanc depuis <literal>ifup</literal>, &nbsp;stop&nbsp; si lanc depuis <literal>ifdown</literal>"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12908
msgid "\"<literal>$PHASE</literal>\""
msgstr "&nbsp;<literal>$PHASE</literal>&nbsp;"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12911
msgid "as per \"<literal>$MODE</literal>\", but with finer granularity, distinguishing the <literal>pre-up</literal>, <literal>post-up</literal>, <literal>pre-down</literal> and <literal>post-down</literal> phases"
msgstr "comme pour &nbsp;<literal>$MODE</literal>&nbsp; mais avec une plus faible granularit permettant de distinguer les phases <literal>pre-up</literal>, <literal>post-up</literal>, <literal>pre-down</literal> et <literal>post-down</literal>"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12916
msgid "\"<literal>$VERBOSITY</literal>\""
msgstr "&nbsp;<literal>$VERBOSITY</literal>&nbsp;"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12919
msgid "indicates whether \"<literal>--verbose</literal>\" was used; set to 1 if so, 0 if not"
msgstr "indique si &nbsp;<literal>--verbose</literal>&nbsp; a t utilis. Positionne  1 dans ce cas,  0 sinon"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12924
msgid "\"<literal>$PATH</literal>\""
msgstr "&nbsp;<literal>$PATH</literal>&nbsp;"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12927
msgid "command search path: \"<literal>/usr/local/sbin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/sbin:/usr/bin:/sbin:/bin</literal>\""
msgstr "chemin de recherche de la commande&nbsp;: &nbsp;<literal>/usr/local/sbin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/sbin:/usr/bin:/sbin:/bin</literal>&nbsp;"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12932
msgid "\"<literal>$IF_&lt;OPTION&gt;</literal>\""
msgstr "&nbsp;<literal>$IF_&lt;OPTION&gt;</literal>&nbsp;"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12935
msgid "value for the corresponding option under the <emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>iface</literal></emphasis> stanza"
msgstr "valeur de l'option correspondante de l'entre <emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>iface</literal></emphasis>"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12941
msgid "Here, each environment variable, \"<literal>$IF_&lt;OPTION&gt;</literal>\", is created from the name for the corresponding option such as &lt;option1&gt; and &lt;option2&gt; by prepending \"<literal>$IF_</literal>\", converting the case to the upper case, replacing hyphens to underscores, and discarding non-alphanumeric characters."
msgstr "Ici, chaque variable d'environnement, &nbsp;<literal>$IF_&lt;OPTION&gt; </literal>&nbsp;, est cre  partir du nom de l'option correspondante comme &lt;option1&gt; et &lt;option2&gt; en les prfixant avec &nbsp;<literal>$IF_</literal>&nbsp;, et en convertissant la casse en majuscules, en remplaant les tirets (&nbsp;-&nbsp;) par des tirets souligns (&nbsp;_&nbsp;) et en supprimant les caractres non alphanumriques."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12943
msgid "See <xref linkend=\"_the_basic_syntax_of_etc_network_interfaces\"/> for &lt;address_family&gt;, &lt;method_name&gt;, &lt;option1&gt; and &lt;option2&gt;."
msgstr "Voir <xref linkend=\"_the_basic_syntax_of_etc_network_interfaces\"/> pour &lt;famille_adresse&gt;, &lt;nom_mthode&gt;, &lt;option1&gt; et &lt;option2&gt;."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12945
msgid "The <literal>ifupdown-extra</literal> package (see <xref linkend=\"_the_ifupdown_extra_package\"/>) uses these environment variables to extend the functionality of the <literal>ifupdown</literal> package.  The <literal>ifmetric</literal> package (see <xref linkend=\"_the_ifmetric_package\"/>) installs the \"<literal>/etc/network/if-up.d/ifmetric</literal>\" script which sets the metric via the \"<literal>$IF_METRIC</literal>\" variable.  The <literal>guessnet</literal> package (see <xref linkend=\"_mapping_with_guessnet\"/>), which provides simple and powerful framework for the auto-selection of the network configuration via the mapping mechanism, also uses these."
msgstr "Le paquet <literal>ifupdown-extra</literal> (voir <xref linkend=\"_the_ifupdown_extra_package\"/>) utilise ces variables d'environnement pour tendre les fonctionnalits du paquet <literal>ifupdown</literal>. Le paquet <literal>ifmetric</literal> (voir <xref linkend= \"_the_ifmetric_package\"/>) installe le script &nbsp;<literal>/etc/network/if-up.d/ifmetric</literal>&nbsp; qui dfinit la mtrique par l'intermdiaire de la variable &nbsp;<literal>$IF_METRIC</literal>&nbsp;. Le paquet <literal>guessnet</literal> (voir <xref linkend=\"_mapping_with_guessnet\"/>), qui fournit une ossature simple et puissante pour la slection automatique de la configuration du rseau par le mcanisme de cartographie de rseau (&nbsp;mapping&nbsp;), les utilise aussi."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12947
msgid "For more specific examples of custom network configuration scripts using these environment variables, you should check example scripts in \"<literal>/usr/share/doc/ifupdown/examples/*</literal>\" and scripts used in <literal>ifscheme</literal> and <literal>ifupdown-scripts-zg2</literal> packages.  These additional scripts have some overlaps of functionalities with basic <literal>ifupdown-extra</literal> and <literal>guessnet</literal> packages.  If you install these additional scripts, you should customize these scripts to avoid interferences."
msgstr "Pour des exemples plus spcifiques de scripts personnaliss de configuration du rseau en utilisant les variables d'environnement, vous pouvez consulter les scripts d'exemples se trouvant dans &nbsp;<literal>/usr/share/doc/ifupdown/examples/*</literal>&nbsp; et les scripts utiliss dans les paquet <literal>ifscheme</literal> et <literal>ifupdown-scripts-zg2</literal>.  Ces scripts supplmentaires ont des fonctionnalits qui se chevauchent un peu avec les paquets de base <literal>ifupdown-extra</literal> et <literal>guessnet</literal>. Si vous installez ces scripts supplmentaires, vous devrez les personnaliser afin d'viter des interfrences."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12951
msgid "Mapping with guessnet"
msgstr "Cartographie rseau avec guessnet"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12952
msgid "Instead of manually choosing configuration as described in <xref linkend=\"_the_manually_switchable_network_configuration\"/>, you can use the mapping mechanism described in <xref linkend=\"_the_mapping_stanza\"/> to select network configuration automatically with custom scripts."
msgstr "Plutt que de choisir manuellement la configuration comme il est dcrit dans la <xref linkend=\"_the_manually_switchable_network_configuration\"/>, vous pouvez utiliser le mcanisme de cartographie rseau dcrit dans la <xref linkend=\"_the_mapping_stanza\"/> pour slectionner automatiquement la configuration du rseau  l'aide de scripts personnaliss."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12953
msgid "The <literal>guessnet-ifupdown</literal>(8) command provided by the <literal>guessnet</literal> package is designed to be used as a mapping script and provides powerful framework to enhance the <literal>ifupdown</literal> system."
msgstr "La commande <literal>guessnet-ifupdown</literal>(8) fournie par le paquet <literal>guessnet</literal> est conue pour tre utilise comme script de cartographie rseau et fournit une infrastructure puissante pour amliorer le systme <literal>ifupdown</literal>."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12957
msgid "You list test condition as the value for <emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>guessnet</literal></emphasis> options for each network configuration under <emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>iface</literal></emphasis> stanza."
msgstr "Vous listez la condition de test comme valeur des options de <emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>guessnet</literal></emphasis> pour chacune des configurations de rseau de l'entre <emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>iface</literal></emphasis>."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12962
msgid "Mapping choses the <emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>iface</literal></emphasis> with first non-ERROR result as the network configuration."
msgstr "La cartographie du rseau choisit la premire entre <emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>iface</literal></emphasis> donnant un rsultat qui ne soit pas en erreur comme configuration du rseau."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12966
msgid "This dual usage of the \"<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>\" file by the mapping script, <literal>guessnet-ifupdown</literal>, and the original network configuration infrastructure, <literal>ifupdown</literal>, does not cause negative impacts since <emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>guessnet</literal></emphasis> options only export extra environment variables to scripts run by the <literal>ifupdown</literal> system.  See details in <literal>guessnet-ifupdown</literal>(8)."
msgstr "Cette double utilisation du fichier &nbsp;<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>&nbsp; par le script de mapping, <literal>guessnet-ifupdown</literal> et l'infrastructure d'origine de configuration du rseau, <literal>ifupdown</literal>, n'a pas d'impact ngatif car les options de <emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>guessnet</literal></emphasis> n'exportent que des variables d'environnement supplmentaires vers les scripts lancs par le systme <literal>ifupdown</literal>.  Voir <literal>guessnet-ifupdown</literal>(8) pour davantage d'informations."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><note><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12968
msgid "When multiple <emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>guessnet</literal></emphasis> option lines are required in \"<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>\", use option lines started with <emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>guessnet1</literal></emphasis>, <emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>guessnet2</literal></emphasis>, and so on, since the <literal>ifupdown</literal> package does not allow starting strings of option lines to be repeated."
msgstr "Lorsqu'il est ncessaire d'avoir plusieurs lignes d'options de <emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>guessnet</literal></emphasis> dans &nbsp;<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>&nbsp;, utilisez les lignes d'options commenant  par <emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>guessnet1</literal></emphasis>, <emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>guessnet2</literal></emphasis> et ainsi de suite, car le paquet <literal>ifupdown</literal> n'autorise pas que les chanes de caractres de dbut des lignes d'options soient dupliques."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12973
msgid "The network configuration for desktop"
msgstr "Configuration rseau pour l'ordinateur de bureau"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12975
msgid "GUI network configuration tools"
msgstr "Outils graphiques de configuration du rseau"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12976
msgid "The capability of default GUI network configuration tools for each desktop environments such as GNOME tends to be limited to basic configurations such as static IP or DHCP.  They actually overwrite contents of \"<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>\" file behind you. Please check how they change \"<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>\" file by yourself."
msgstr "Les possibilits de l'interface graphique des outils de configuration du rseau de tous les environnements de bureau tels que GNOME on tendance  tre limites  des configurations de base telles que les IP statiques ou le DHCP. Elles crasent en fait le contenu de &nbsp;<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>&nbsp; que vous aviez fait. Veuillez contrler vous-mme ce qu'elles ont modifi dans &nbsp;<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>&nbsp;."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><caution><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12978
msgid "They may not understand complicated advanced configuration done manually in \"<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>\" file."
msgstr "Ils peuvent ne pas comprendre les configurations avances effectues manuellement dans le fichier &nbsp;<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>&nbsp;."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12982
msgid "Automatic network configuration"
msgstr "Configuration automatique du rseau"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12983
msgid "There are independent automatic network configuration tools, such as <ulink url=\"&networkmanagernm;\">NetworkManager (NM)</ulink> (<literal>network-manager</literal> and associated packages) and <ulink url=\"&wicd;\">Wicd</ulink> (<literal>wicd</literal> package) which manage network connection via <ulink url=\"&daemon;\">daemon</ulink> independent of the <literal>ifupdown</literal> package. They allow easy management of wireless connections.  These come with its own nice GUI user interfaces."
msgstr "Il existe des outils indpendant pour la configuration automatique du rseau, comme <ulink url=\"&networkmanagernm;\">NetworkManager (NM)</ulink> (<literal>network-manager</literal> et les paquets associs) et <ulink url=\"&wicd;\">Wicd</ulink> (paquet<literal>wicd</literal>) qui grent la connexion au rseau par l'intermdiaire d'un <ulink url=\"&daemon;\">dmon</ulink> qui ne dpend pas du paquet  <literal>ifupdown</literal>. Ils permettent une gestion facile des connexions sans fil. Ils ont leur propre superbe interface utilisateur graphique."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><warning><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12985
msgid "Do not use these automatic network configuration tools for servers.  These are aimed primarily for mobile desktop users on laptops."
msgstr "Ne pas utiliser ces outils de configuration automatique du rseau sur un serveur. Ils ont t prvus principalement pour les utilisateurs de systme de bureau tournant sur des ordinateurs portables."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><warning><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12988
msgid "These automatic network configuration tools are moving targets and documentation here is likely to be incorrect for <literal>squeeze</literal>.  So be warned."
msgstr "Ces outils de configuration automatiques du rseau voluent rapidement et cette documentation sera probablement incorrecte pour <literal>squeeze </literal>. Faites donc attention."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><caution><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12991
msgid "These automatic network configuration tools may not be compatible with esoteric configurations of <literal>ifupdown</literal> in \"<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>\" such as ones in <xref linkend=\"_the_basic_network_configuration_with_ifupdown\"/> and <xref linkend=\"_the_advanced_network_configuration_with_ifupdown\"/>.  Having even \"<literal>hostname</literal>\" stanza for DHCP controlled interface as described in <xref linkend=\"_the_network_interface_served_by_the_dhcp\"/> caused NM to ignore such interface in <literal>lenny</literal>. Check <ulink url=\"&btsofnetworkmanager;\">BTS of network-manager</ulink> and <ulink url=\"&btsofwicd;\">BTS of wicd</ulink> for current issues and limitations."
msgstr "Ces outils de configuration automatique peuvent ne pas tre compatibles avec des configurations sotriques de <literal>ifupdown</literal> dans &nbsp;<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>&nbsp; telles que celles se trouvant en <xref linkend=\"_the_basic_network_configuration_with_ifupdown\"/> et <xref linkend=\"_the_advanced_network_configuration_with_ifupdown\"/>. Le fait d'avoir une entre &nbsp;<literal>hostname</literal>&nbsp; pour une interface contrle par DHCP comme dcrit dans la <xref linkend=\"_the_network_interface_served_by_the_dhcp\"/> fait que NM ignore une telle interface avec <literal>lenny</literal>. Vrifiez le <ulink url=\"&btsofnetworkmanager;\">BTS de network-manager</ulink> et le <ulink url=\"&btsofwicd;\">BTS de wicd</ulink> pour les problmes et les limitations actuels."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12993
msgid "The configuration of NM is described in \"<literal>/usr/share/doc/network-manager/README.Debian</literal>\".  Essentially this is as follows."
msgstr "La configuration de NM est dcrite dans &nbsp;<literal>/usr/share/doc/network-manager/README.Debian</literal>&nbsp;. Elle consiste principalement en ce qui suit&nbsp;:"

