# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:15570
msgid "Use of DSA key for SSH-2 is deprecated because key is smaller and slow. There are no more reasons to work around RSA patent using DSA since it has been expired.  DSA stands for <ulink url=\"&digitalsignaturealgorithm;\">Digital Signature Algorithm</ulink> and slow. Also see <ulink url=\"&dsabfhbb;\">DSA-1571-1</ulink>."
msgstr "L'utilisation de cls DSA pour SSH-2 est obsolte parce que la cl est plus courte et lente. Il n'y a plus de raison de contourner le brevet de RSA en utilisant DSA parce qu'il est arriv en fin de validit. DSA signifie <ulink url=\"&digitalsignaturealgorithm;\">Digital Signature Algorithm</ulink> (Algorithme de signature numrique) et il est lent. Voir aussi <ulink url=\"&dsabfhbb;\">DSA-1571-1</ulink>."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:15573
msgid "For \"<literal>HostbasedAuthentication</literal>\" to work in SSH-2, you must adjust the settings of \"<literal>HostbasedAuthentication</literal>\" to \"<literal>yes</literal>\" in both \"<literal>/etc/ssh/sshd_config</literal>\" on the server host and \"<literal>/etc/ssh/ssh_config</literal>\" or \"<literal>~/.ssh/config</literal>\" on the client host."
msgstr "Pour que &nbsp;<literal>HostbasedAuthentication</literal>&nbsp; fonctionne avec SSH-2, vous devez dfinir les paramtres de &nbsp;<literal>HostbasedAuthentication</literal>&nbsp;  &nbsp;<literal>yes</literal>&nbsp;  la fois dans le fichier &nbsp;<literal>/etc/ssh/sshd_config</literal>&nbsp; sur la machine serveur et dans le fichier &nbsp;<literal>/etc/ssh/ssh_config</literal>&nbsp; ou &nbsp;<literal>~/.ssh/config</literal>&nbsp; sur la machine client."

