#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:17881
msgid "<ulink url=\"&multilingualizatelanguagesupport;\">Multilingualization (M17N) or Native Language Support</ulink> for an application software is done in 2 steps."
msgstr "Le <ulink url=\"&multilingualizatelanguagesupport;\">multilinguisme (M17N) ou la gestion de la langue natale (&nbsp;Native Language Support&nbsp;)</ulink> d'un logiciel applicatif est ralis en deux tapes&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:17885
msgid "Internationalization (I18N): To make a software potentially handle multiple locales."
msgstr "L'internationalisation (I18N)&nbsp;: donne la possibilit  un logiciel de grer plusieurs paramtres linguistiques&nbsp;;"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:17890
msgid "Localization (L10N): To make a software handle an specific locale."
msgstr "La localisation (L10N)&nbsp;: permet au logiciel de prendre en charge des paramtres linguistiques particuliers."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:17895
msgid "There are 17, 18, or 10 letters between \"m\" and \"n\", \"i\" and \"n\", or \"l\" and \"n\" in multilingualization, internationalization, and localization which correspond to M17N, I18N, and L10N."
msgstr "Il y a 17, 18, ou 10 lettres entre &nbsp;m&nbsp; et &nbsp;n&nbsp;, &nbsp;i&nbsp; et &nbsp;n&nbsp; ou &nbsp;l&nbsp; et &nbsp;n&nbsp; dans &nbsp;multilingualization&nbsp;, &nbsp;internationalization&nbsp; et &nbsp;localization&nbsp; ce qui correspond  M17N, I18N, et L10N."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:17897
msgid "The modern software such as GNOME and KDE are multilingualized.  They are internationalized by making them handle <ulink url=\"&utfi;\">UTF-8</ulink> data and localized by providing their translated messages through the <literal>gettext</literal>(1) infrastructure.  Translated messages may be provided as separate localization packages.  They can be selected simply by setting pertinent environment variables to the appropriate locale."
msgstr "Des logiciels modernes, tels que GNOME et KDE, grent le multilinguisme. Ils sont internationaliss en les faisant grer les donnes <ulink url=\"&utfi;\">UTF-8</ulink> et localiss en leur donnant les messages traduits par l'intermdiaire de l'infrastructure <literal>gettext</literal>(1). Les messages traduits peuvent tre offerts sous forme de paquets de localisation spars. Il sont simplement  slectionns en donnant la valeur du paramtres linguistique appropri  des variables d'environnement pertinentes."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:17898
msgid "The simplest representation of the text data is <emphasis role=\"strong\">ASCII</emphasis> which is sufficient for English and uses less than 127 characters (representable with 7 bits).  In order to support much more characters for the international support, many character encoding systems have been invented.  The modern and sensible encoding system is <emphasis role=\"strong\">UTF-8</emphasis> which can handle practically all the characters known to the human (see <xref linkend=\"_basics_of_encoding\"/>)."
msgstr "La reprsentation la plus simple d'un texte de donnes est l'<emphasis role=\"strong\">ASCII</emphasis> qui suffit  l'anglais et utilise moins de 127 caractres (qui peuvent tre reprsents avec 7 bits). De manire  pouvoir prendre en compte bien plus de caractres pour l'internationalisation, de nombreux systmes de codage des caractres ont t invents. Le systme moderne et prfr est <emphasis role=\"strong\">UTF-8</emphasis> qui peut prendre en charge tous les caractres connus des tres humains (voir <xref linkend=\"_basics_of_encoding\"/>)."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:17899
msgid "See <ulink url=\"&introductiontoibin;\">Introduction to i18n</ulink> for details."
msgstr "Voir <ulink url=\"&introductiontoibin;\">Introduction  i18n</ulink> pour davantage d'informations."

