# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19284
msgid "<ulink url=\"&extd;\">Ext3</ulink> filesystem is the default filesystem for the Linux system and strongly recommended to use it unless you have some specific reasons not to.  After Linux kernel 2.6.30 (Debian <literal>squeeze</literal>), <ulink url=\"&exte;\">ext4</ulink> filesystem is available and expected to be the default filesystem for the Linux system.  <ulink url=\"&btrfs;\">btrfs</ulink> filesystem is expected to be the next default filesystem after <ulink url=\"&exte;\">ext4</ulink> filesystem for the Linux system."
msgstr "Le systme de fichiers <ulink url=\"&extd;\">ext3</ulink> est le systme de fichiers par dfaut du systme Linux et il est fortement recommand de l'utiliser  moins que vous n'ayez des raisons spcifiques pour ne pas le faire. Aprs le noyau Linux 2.6.30 (Debian <literal>squeeze</literal>), le systme de fichiers <ulink url=\"&exte;\">ext4</ulink> sera disponible et devrait tre le systme de fichiers par dfaut d'un systme Linux. Le systme de fichiers par dfaut pour le systme Linux aprs <ulink url=\"&exte;\">ext4</ulink> devrait tre <ulink url=\"&btrfs;\">btrfs</ulink>."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><warning><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19287
msgid "You might face some limitations with ext4 since it is new.  For example, you must have Linux kernel 2.6.30 or later if you wish to resize an ext4 partition."
msgstr "Vous rencontrez peut-tre quelques limitations avec ext4 parce qu'il est rcent.  Par exemple vous devrez avoir un noyau de Linux 2.6.30 si vous dsirez redimensionner une partition ext4."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19290
msgid "Some tools allow access to filesystem without Linux kernel support (see <xref linkend=\"_manipulating_files_without_mounting_disk\"/>)."
msgstr "Certains outils permettent l'accs au systme de fichiers sans prise en charge par le noyau Linux (voir <xref linkend=\"_manipulating_files_without_mounting_disk\"/>)."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19294
msgid "Filesystem creation and integrity check"
msgstr "Cration et vrification de l'intgrit d'un systme de fichiers"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19295
msgid "The <literal>mkfs</literal>(8) command creates the filesystem on a Linux system. The <literal>fsck</literal>(8) command provides the filesystem integrity check and repair on a Linux system."
msgstr "La commande <literal>mkfs</literal>(8) permet de crer un systme de fichiers sur un systme Linux. La commande <literal>fsck</literal>(8) permet de vrifier l'intgrit du systme de fichiers et de le rparer sur un systme Linux."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><caution><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19297
msgid "It is generally not safe to run <literal>fsck</literal> on <emphasis role=\"strong\">mounted filesystems</emphasis>."
msgstr "En gnral, il n'est pas sr de faire tourner <literal>fsck</literal> sur un <emphasis role=\"strong\">systme de fichiers mont</emphasis>."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19300
msgid "Check files in \"<literal>/var/log/fsck/</literal>\" for the result of the <literal>fsck</literal>(8) command run from the boot script."
msgstr "Vous trouverez les rsultats de la commande <literal>fsck</literal>(8) lancez depuis le script de dmarrage dans &nbsp;<literal>/var/log/fsck/</literal>&nbsp;."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19303
msgid "Use \"<literal>shutdown -F -r now</literal>\" to force to run the <literal>fsck</literal>(8) command safely on all filesystems including root filesystem on reboot. See the <literal>shutdown</literal>(8) manpage for more."
msgstr "Utilisez &nbsp;<literal>shutdown -F -r now</literal>&nbsp; pour forcer l'excution sre de la commande <literal>fsck</literal>(8) sur tous les systmes de fichiers, y-compris le systme de fichiers racine lors du redmarrage. Voir la page de manuel <literal>shutdown</literal>(8) pour davantage d'informations."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19307
msgid "Optimization of filesystem by mount options"
msgstr "Optimisation du systme de fichiers  l'aide des options de montage"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19308
msgid "Performance and characteristics of a filesystem can be optimized by mount options used on it (see <literal>fstab</literal>(5) and <literal>mount</literal>(8)).  Notable ones are the following."
msgstr "Les performances et les caractristiques d'un systme de fichiers peuvent tre optimises  l'aide des options de montage utilises (voir <literal>fstab</literal>(5) et <literal>mount</literal>(8)). Les principales options sont les suivantes&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19312
msgid "\"<literal>defaults</literal>\" option implies default options: \"<literal>rw,suid,dev,exec,auto,nouser,async</literal>\". (general)"
msgstr "l'option &nbsp;<literal>defaults</literal>&nbsp; implique les options par dfaut&nbsp;: &nbsp;<literal>rw,suid,dev,exec,auto,nouser,async</literal>&nbsp; (gnral)"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19317
msgid "\"<literal>noatime</literal>\" or \"<literal>relatime</literal>\" option is very effective for speeding up the read access. (general)"
msgstr "les options &nbsp;<literal>noatime</literal>&nbsp; ou &nbsp;<literal>relatime</literal>&nbsp; sont trs efficace pour acclrer la vitesse de lecture (gnral)."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19322
msgid "\"<literal>user</literal>\" option allows an ordinary user to mount the filesystem. This option implies \"<literal>noexec,nosuid,nodev</literal>\" option combination. (general, used for CD and floppy)"
msgstr "l'option &nbsp;<literal>user</literal>&nbsp; permet  un utilisateur normal de monter le systme de fichiers. Cette option implique la combinaison d'option &nbsp;<literal>noexec,nosuid,nodev</literal>&nbsp; (gnral, utilise pour les CD et les disquettes)"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19327
msgid "\"<literal>noexec,nodev,nosuid</literal>\" option combination is used to enhance security. (general)"
msgstr "La combinaisons d'options &nbsp;<literal>noexec,nodev,nosuid</literal>&nbsp; est utilise pour amliorer la scurit (gnral)."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19332
msgid "\"<literal>noauto</literal>\" option limits mounting by explicit operation only. (general)"
msgstr "l'option &nbsp;<literal>noauto</literal>&nbsp; limite le montage uniquement  une opration explicite (gnral)."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19337
msgid "\"<literal>data=journal</literal>\" option for ext3fs can enhance data integrity against power failure with some loss of write speed."
msgstr "l'option &nbsp;<literal>data=journal</literal>&nbsp; pour ext3fs peut amliorer l'intgrit des donnes lors d'une panne de courant, elle s'accompagne d'une lgre baisse de la vitesse d'criture."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19342
msgid "You need to provide kernel boot parameter (see <xref linkend=\"_stage_2_the_boot_loader\"/>), e.g. \"<literal>rootflags=data=journal</literal>\" to deploy a non-default journaling mode for the root filesystem.  For <literal>lenny</literal>, the default jounaling mode is \"<literal>rootflags=data=ordered</literal>\".  For <literal>squeeze</literal>, it is \"<literal>rootflags=data=writeback</literal>\"."
msgstr "Vous devez donner au noyau le paramtre de dmarrage (voir <xref linkend=\"_stage_2_the_boot_loader\"/>), par exemple &nbsp;<literal>rootflags=data=journal</literal>&nbsp; afin de mettre en uvre pour le systme de fichiers racine un mode de journalisation autre que celui par dfaut. Pour <literal>lenny</literal>, le mode de journalisation par dfaut est &nbsp;<literal>rootflags=data=ordered</literal>&nbsp;. Pour <literal>squeeze</literal>, il s'agit de &nbsp;<literal>rootflags=data=writeback</literal>&nbsp;."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19346
msgid "Optimization of filesystem via superblock"
msgstr "Optimisation du systme de fichier  l'aide du superbloc"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19347
msgid "Characteristics of a filesystem can be optimized via its superblock using the <literal>tune2fs</literal>(8) command."
msgstr "Les caractristiques du systme de fichiers peuvent tre optimises par l'intermdiaire de sont superbloc en utilisant la commande <literal>tune2fs</literal>(8)."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19351
msgid "Execution of \"<literal>sudo tune2fs -l /dev/hda1</literal>\" displays the contents of the filesystem superblock on \"<literal>/dev/hda1</literal>\"."
msgstr "L'excution de &nbsp;<literal>sudo tune2fs -l /dev/hda1</literal>&nbsp; affiche le contenu du superbloc du systme de fichiers situ sur &nbsp;<literal>/dev/hda1</literal>&nbsp;."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19356
msgid "Execution of \"<literal>sudo tune2fs -c 50 /dev/hda1</literal>\" changes frequency of filesystem checks (<literal>fsck</literal> execution during boot-up) to every 50 boots on \"<literal>/dev/hda1</literal>\"."
msgstr "L'excution de &nbsp;<literal>sudo tune2fs -c 50 /dev/hda1</literal>&nbsp; modifie la frquence de des vrifications du systme de fichiers (excution de <literal>fsck</literal> lors du dmarrage)  50 dmarrage sur &nbsp;<literal>/dev/hda1</literal>&nbsp;."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19361
msgid "Execution of \"<literal>sudo tune2fs -j /dev/hda1</literal>\" adds journaling capability to the filesystem, i.e. filesystem conversion from <ulink url=\"&extc;\">ext2</ulink> to <ulink url=\"&extd;\">ext3</ulink> on \"<literal>/dev/hda1</literal>\".  (Do this on the unmounted filesystem.)"
msgstr "L'excution de la commande &nbsp;<literal>sudo tune2fs -j /dev/hda1</literal>&nbsp; ajoute la possibilit de journalisation au systme de fichiers, c'est--dire la conversion de systme de fichiers de <ulink url=\"&extc;\">ext2</ulink> vers <ulink url=\"&extd;\">ext3</ulink> sur &nbsp;<literal>/dev/hda1</literal>&nbsp;. (Effectuez ceci sur un systme de fichier non mont)."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19366
msgid "Execution of \"<literal>sudo tune2fs -O extents,uninit_bg,dir_index /dev/hda1 &amp;&amp; fsck -pf /dev/hda1</literal>\" converts it from <ulink url=\"&extd;\">ext3</ulink> to <ulink url=\"&exte;\">ext4</ulink> on \"<literal>/dev/hda1</literal>\".  (Do this on the unmounted filesystem.)"
msgstr "L'excution de &nbsp;<literal>sudo tune2fs -O extents,uninit_bg,dir_index /dev/hda1 &amp;&amp; fsck -pf /dev/hda1</literal>&nbsp; le convertit de <ulink url=\"&extd;\">ext3</ulink> vers <ulink url=\"&exte;\">ext4</ulink> sur &nbsp;<literal>/dev/hda1</literal>&nbsp;. ( effectuer sur un systme de fichiers non mont)."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19371
msgid "Filesystem conversion for the boot device to the <ulink url=\"&exte;\">ext4</ulink> filesystem should be avoided until <ulink url=\"&grubbootloadersutefilesystemwell;\">GRUB boot loader supports the ext4 filesystem well</ulink> and installed Linux Kernel version is newer than 2.6.30."
msgstr "La conversion du systme de fichier du priphrique de dmarrage vers le systme de fichiers <ulink url=\"&exte;\">ext4</ulink> doit tre vite jusqu' ce que le <ulink url=\"&grubbootloadersutefilesystemwell;\">systme d'amorage GRUB prennent correctement en charge le systme de fichiers ext4</ulink> et que la version de noyau installe soit plus rcente que 2.6.30."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19374
msgid "Despite its name, <literal>tune2fs</literal>(8) works not only on the <ulink url=\"&extc;\">ext2</ulink> filesystem but also on the <ulink url=\"&extd;\">ext3</ulink> and <ulink url=\"&exte;\">ext4</ulink> filesystems."
msgstr "En dpit de son nom, <literal>tune2fs</literal>(8) ne fonctionne pas uniquement sur le systme de fichiers <ulink url=\"&extc;\">ext2</ulink> mais aussi sur les systmes de fichiers <ulink url=\"&extd;\">ext3</ulink> et <ulink url=\"&exte;\">ext4</ulink>."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19378
msgid "Optimization of hard disk"
msgstr "Optimisation du disque dur"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19380
msgid "Please check your hardware and read manpage of <literal>hdparam</literal>(8) before playing with hard disk configuration because this may be quite dangerous for the data integrity."
msgstr "Veuillez vrifier votre matriel et lire la page de manuel <literal>hdparam</literal>(8) avant de jouer avec la configuration de vos disques durs parce que ce peut tre assez dangereux pour l'intgrit des donnes."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19382
msgid "You can test disk access speed of a hard disk, e.g. \"<literal>/dev/hda</literal>\", by \"<literal>hdparm -tT /dev/hda</literal>\". For some hard disk connected with (E)IDE, you can speed it up with \"<literal>hdparm -q -c3 -d1 -u1 -m16 /dev/hda</literal>\" by enabling the \"(E)IDE 32-bit I/O support\", enabling the \"using_dma flag\", setting \"interrupt-unmask flag\", and setting the \"multiple 16 sector I/O\" (dangerous!)."
msgstr "Vous pouvez tester la vitesse de lecture d'un disque dur, par exemple &nbsp;<literal>/dev/hda</literal>&nbsp; par &nbsp;<literal>hdparm -tT /dev/hda</literal>&nbsp;. Vous pouvez acclrer certains disques (E)IDE avec &nbsp;<literal>hdparm -q -c3 -d1 -u1 -m16 /dev/hda</literal>&nbsp; en activant la prise en charge des E/S 32 bits (&nbsp;(E)IDE 32-bit I/O support&nbsp;, en positionnant l'indicateur d'utilisation de dma &nbsp;using_dma flag&nbsp;, en positionnant l'indicateur de dmasquage des interruptions (&nbsp;interrupt-unmask flag&nbsp;) et en positionnant les E/S multiples sur 15 secteurs (&nbsp;multiple 16 sector I/O&nbsp; (dangereux&nbsp;!)."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19383
msgid "You can test write cache feature of a hard disk, e.g. \"<literal>/dev/sda</literal>\", by \"<literal>hdparm -W /dev/sda</literal>\". You can disable its write cache feature with \"<literal>hdparm -W 0 /dev/sda</literal>\"."
msgstr "Vous pouvez tester la fonctionnalit de cache d'un disque dur, par exemple &nbsp;<literal>/dev/sda</literal>&nbsp; par &nbsp;<literal>hdparm -W /dev/sda</literal>&nbsp;. Vous pouvez dsactiver le cache en criture avec &nbsp;<literal>hdparm -W 0 /dev/sda</literal>&nbsp;."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19384
msgid "You may be able to read badly pressed CDROMs on modern high speed CD-ROM drive by slowing it down with \"<literal>setcd -x 2</literal>\"."
msgstr "Vous pouvez russir  lire un CD-ROM vraiment mal press sur un lecteur de CD-ROM moderne rapide en le ralentissant avec &nbsp;<literal>setcd -x 2</literal>&nbsp;."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19387
msgid "Using SMART to predict hard disk failure"
msgstr "Utiliser SMART pour prdire les dfaillances des disques durs"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19388
msgid "You can monitor and log your hard disk which is compliant to <ulink url=\"&smart;\">SMART</ulink> with the <literal>smartd</literal>(8) daemon."
msgstr "Vous pouvez surveiller et enregistrer les disques durs conformes  <ulink url=\"&smart;\">SMART</ulink>  l'aide du dmon <literal>smartd</literal>(8)."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19392
msgid "Enable <ulink url=\"&smart;\">SMART</ulink> feature in <ulink url=\"&bios;\">BIOS</ulink>."
msgstr "Activez la fonctionnalit <ulink url=\"&smart;\">SMART</ulink> dans le <ulink url=\"&bios;\">BIOS</ulink>."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19397
msgid "Install the <literal>smartmontools</literal> package."
msgstr "Installez le paquet <literal>smartmontools</literal>."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19402
msgid "Identify your hard disk drives by listing them with <literal>df</literal>(1)."
msgstr "Identifiez vos disques durs en en affichant la liste avec <literal>df</literal>(1)."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19407
msgid "Let's assume a hard disk drive to be monitored as \"<literal>/dev/hda</literal>\"."
msgstr "Supposons que le disque dut  surveiller soit &nbsp;<literal>/dev/hda</literal>&nbsp;."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19414
msgid "Check the output of \"<literal>smartctl -a /dev/hda</literal>\" to see if <ulink url=\"&smart;\">SMART</ulink> feature is actually enabled."
msgstr "Contrlez la sortie de &nbsp;<literal>smartctl -a /dev/hda</literal>&nbsp; pour voir si la fonctionnalit <ulink url=\"&smart;\">SMART</ulink> est effectivement active."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19419
msgid "If not, enable it by \"<literal>smartctl -s on -a /dev/hda</literal>\"."
msgstr "Si elle ne l'est pas, activez-la avec &nbsp;<literal>smartctl -s on -a /dev/hda</literal>&nbsp;."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19426
msgid "Enable <literal>smartd</literal>(8) daemon to run by the following."
msgstr "Autorisez le fonctionnement du dmon <literal>smartd</literal>(8) par l'action suivante&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19431
msgid "uncomment \"<literal>start_smartd=yes</literal>\" in the \"<literal>/etc/default/smartmontools</literal>\" file."
msgstr "dcommentez &nbsp;<literal>start_smartd=yes</literal>&nbsp; dans le fichier &nbsp;<literal>/etc/default/smartmontools</literal>&nbsp;&nbsp;;"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19436
msgid "restart the <literal>smartd</literal>(8) daemon by \"<literal>sudo /etc/init.d/smartmontools restart</literal>\"."
msgstr "relancez le dmon <literal>smartd</literal>(8) avec &nbsp;<literal>sudo /etc/init.d/smartmontools restart</literal>&nbsp;."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19443
msgid "The <literal>smartd</literal>(8) daemon can be customized with the <literal>/etc/smartd.conf</literal> file including how to be notified of warnings."
msgstr "Le dmon <literal>smartd</literal>(8) peut tre personnalis par l'intermdiaire du fichier <literal>/etc/smartd.conf</literal> y-compris la manire d'tre inform des avertissements."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19447
msgid "Expansion of usable storage space via LVM"
msgstr "tendre l'espace de stockage utile  l'aide de LVM"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19448
msgid "For partitions created on <ulink url=\"&logicalvolumemanagerlvm;\">Logical Volume Manager (LVM)</ulink> (Linux feature) at install time, they can be resized easily by concatenating extents onto them or truncating extents from them over multiple storage devices without major system reconfiguration."
msgstr "Les partitions cres sur le <ulink url=\"&logicalvolumemanagerlvm;\">gestionnaire de volumes logiques (LVM)</ulink> (&nbsp;Logical Volume Manager&nbsp;) (fonctionnalit de Linux) au moment de l'installation peuvent tre facilement redimensionnes en y concatnant des extensions (&nbsp;extents&nbsp;) ou en en tronquant les extensions sur plusieurs priphriques de stockage sans reconfiguration majeure du systme."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19450
msgid "Deployment of the current LVM system may degrade guarantee against filesystem corruption offered by journaled filesystems such as ext3fs unless their system performance is sacrificed by disabling write cache of hard disk."
msgstr "Le dploiement du systme LVM actuel peut dgrader la robustesse aux corruptions du systme de fichiers offert par les systmes de fichiers journaliss tels que ext3fs  moins que les performances du systme ne soient sacrifies en dsactivant le cache d'criture des disques durs."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19454
msgid "Expansion of usable storage space by mounting another partition"
msgstr "Extension de l'espace de stockage en montant une autre partition"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19455
msgid "If you have an empty partition (e.g., \"<literal>/dev/sdx</literal>\"), you can format it with <literal>mkfs.ext3</literal>(1) and <literal>mount</literal>(8) it to a directory where you need more space. (You need to copy original data contents.)"
msgstr "Si vous avez une partition vide (par exemple &nbsp;<literal>/dev/sdx</literal>&nbsp;), vous pouvez la formater avec <literal>mkfs.ext3</literal>(1) et la monter (&nbsp;<literal>mount</literal>(8)&nbsp;) sur un rpertoire o vous avez besoin de davantage d'espace (vous devrez copier les donnes d'origine)."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19456
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ sudo mv work-dir old-dir\n"
"$ sudo mkfs.ext3 /dev/sdx\n"
"$ sudo mount -t ext3 /dev/sdx work-dir\n"
"$ sudo cp -a old-dir/* work-dir\n"
"$ sudo rm -rf old-dir"
msgstr ""
"$ sudo mv rpertoire-travail ancien-rpertoire\n"
"$ sudo mkfs.ext3 /dev/sdx\n"
"$ sudo mount -t ext3 /dev/sdx rpertoire-travail\n"
"$ sudo cp -a ancien-rpertoire/* rpertoire-travail\n"
"$ sudo rm -rf ancien-rpertoire"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19462
msgid "You may alternatively mount an empty disk image file (see <xref linkend=\"_making_the_empty_disk_image_file\"/>) as a loop device (see <xref linkend=\"_mounting_the_disk_image_file\"/>).  The actual disk usage grows with the actual data stored."
msgstr "Vous pouvez aussi monter un fichier image de disque vide (voir <xref linkend=\"_making_the_empty_disk_image_file\"/>) en tant que priphrique de rebouclage(voir <xref linkend=\"_mounting_the_disk_image_file\"/>). L'utilisation relle du disque crot avec les donnes rellement enregistres."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19466
msgid "Expansion of usable storage space using symlink"
msgstr "Extension de l'espace utilisable  l'aide de liens symboliques"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19467
msgid "If you have an empty directory (e.g., \"<literal>/path/to/emp-dir</literal>\") in another partition with usable space, you can create a symlink to the directory with <literal>ln</literal>(8)."
msgstr "Si vous avez un rpertoire vide (par exemple, &nbsp;<literal>/path/to/emp-dir</literal>&nbsp;) dans une autre partition avec de l'espace disponible, vous pouvez crer un lien symbolique vers ce rpertoire avec <literal>ln</literal>(8)."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19468
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ sudo mv work-dir old-dir\n"
"$ sudo mkdir -p /path/to/emp-dir\n"
"$ sudo ln -sf /path/to/emp-dir work-dir\n"
"$ sudo cp -a old-dir/* work-dir\n"
"$ sudo rm -rf old-dir"
msgstr ""
"$ sudo mv rpertoire-travail ancien-rpertoire\n"
"$ sudo mkdir -p /chemin/vers/rpertoire-temporaire\n"
"$ sudo ln -sf /chemin/vers/rpertoire-temporaire rpertoire-travail \n"
"$ sudo cp -a ancien-rpertoire/* rpertoire-travail \n"
"$ sudo rm -rf ancien-rpertoire"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><caution><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19474
msgid "Some software may not function well with \"symlink to a directory\"."
msgstr "Certains logiciels peuvent ne pas bien fonctionner avec des &nbsp;liens symboliques vers un rpertoire&nbsp;."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19478
msgid "Expansion of usable storage space using aufs"
msgstr "Extension de l'espace utilisable  l'aide de aufs"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19479
msgid "If you have usable space in another partition (e.g., \"<literal>/path/to/</literal>\"), you can create a directory in it and stack that on to a directory where you need space with <ulink url=\"&aufs;\">aufs</ulink>."
msgstr "Si vous avez de l'espace disponible dans une autre partition (par exemple &nbsp;<literal>/chemin/vers/</literal>&nbsp;), vous pouvez y crer un rpertoire et empiler cela vers un rpertoire o vous avez besoin de place avec <ulink url=\"&aufs;\">aufs</ulink>."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19480
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ sudo mv work-dir old-dir\n"
"$ sudo mkdir work-dir\n"
"$ sudo mkdir -p /path/to/emp-dir\n"
"$ sudo mount -t aufs -o br:/path/to/emp-dir:old-dir none work-dir"
msgstr ""
"$ sudo mv rpertoire-travail ancien-rpertoire\n"
"$ sudo mkdir rpertoire-travail\n"
"$ sudo mkdir -p /chemin/vers/rpertoire/temporaire\n"
"$ sudo mount -t aufs -o br:/chemin/vers/rpertoire/temporaire:ancien-rpertoire none rpertoire-travail"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><caution><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19485
msgid "Use of <ulink url=\"&aufs;\">aufs</ulink> for long term data storage is not good idea since it is under development and its design change may introduce issues."
msgstr "L'utilisation de <ulink url=\"&aufs;\">aufs</ulink> pour le stockage de donnes  long terme n'est pas une bonne ide car il est en cours de dveloppement et les modifications de sa conceptions peuvent poser des problmes."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19488
msgid "In order to use <ulink url=\"&aufs;\">aufs</ulink>, its utility package <literal>aufs-tools</literal> and kernel module package for <ulink url=\"&aufs;\">aufs</ulink> such as <literal>aufs-modules-2.6-amd64</literal> need to be installed."
msgstr "De manire  pouvoir utiliser <ulink url=\"&aufs;\">aufs</ulink>, il faut installer son paquet utilitaire <literal>aufs-tools</literal> et le paquet des modules du noyau pour <ulink url=\"&aufs;\">aufs</ulink> comme <literal>aufs-modules-2.6-amd64</literal>."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19491
msgid "<ulink url=\"&aufs;\">aufs</ulink> is used to provide writable root filesystem by many modern <ulink url=\"&livecd;\">live CD</ulink> projects."
msgstr "<ulink url=\"&aufs;\">aufs</ulink> est utilis pour fournir un systme de fichiers o l'administrateur peut crire par de nombreux projets de <ulink url=\"&livecd;\">live CD</ulink>."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19496
msgid "Data encryption tips"
msgstr "Astuces de chiffrement des donnes"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19497
msgid "With physical access to your PC, anyone can easily gain root privilege and access all the files on your PC (see <xref linkend=\"_securing_the_root_password\"/>).  This means that login password system can not secure your private and sensitive data against possible theft of your PC.  You must deploy data encryption technology to do it.  Although <ulink url=\"&gnuprivacyguard;\">GNU privacy guard</ulink> (see <xref linkend=\"_data_security_infrastructure\"/>) can encrypt files, it takes some user efforts."
msgstr "Avec un accs physique  votre PC, n'importe qui peut facilement obtenir les privilges de l'administrateur et accder  tous les fichiers de votre PC (voir <xref linkend=\"_securing_the_root_password\"/>). Ceci signifie qu'un systme mot de passe de connexion ne permet pas de scuriser vos donnes personnelles ou sensibles en cas de vol de votre PC. Vous devez dployer des technologies de de chiffrements des donnes  pour assurer cette protection. Bien que <ulink url=\"&gnuprivacyguard;\">GNU privacy guard</ulink> (voir <xref linkend=\"_data_security_infrastructure\"/>) puisse chiffrer des fichiers, il demande quelques efforts de la part de l'utilisateur."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19498
msgid "<ulink url=\"&dmcrypt;\">dm-crypt</ulink> and <ulink url=\"&ecryptfs;\">eCryptfs</ulink> facilitates automatic data encryption natively via Linux kernel modules with minimal user efforts."
msgstr "<ulink url=\"&dmcrypt;\">dm-crypt</ulink> et <ulink url=\"&ecryptfs;\">eCryptfs</ulink> facilitent de manire native le chiffrement automatique des donnes par l'intermdiaire de modules du noyau de Linux avec un minimum d'efforts de la part de l'utilisateur."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19500
msgid "List of data encryption utilities"
msgstr "Liste d'utilitaires de chiffrement des donnes"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19528
msgid "utilities for encrypted block device (<ulink url=\"&dmcrypt;\">dm-crypt</ulink> / <ulink url=\"&luks;\">LUKS</ulink>)"
msgstr "utilitaires pour chiffrer un priphrique en mode bloc (<ulink url=\"&dmcrypt;\">dm-crypt</ulink> / <ulink url=\"&luks;\">LUKS</ulink>)"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19536
msgid "utilities for encrypted block device (<ulink url=\"&dmcrypt;\">dm-crypt</ulink> / <ulink url=\"&luks;\">LUKS</ulink>) with focus on mount/unmount by normal users"
msgstr "utilitaires pour chiffrer un priphrique en mode bloc (<ulink url=\"&dmcrypt;\">dm-crypt</ulink> / <ulink url=\"&luks;\">LUKS</ulink>), l'accent tant mis sur le montage et le dmontage par un utilisateur normal"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19544
msgid "utilities for encrypted stacked filesystem (<ulink url=\"&ecryptfs;\">eCryptfs</ulink>)"
msgstr "utilitaires pour systmes de fichiers empils (&nbsp;stackable&nbsp; chiffrs (<ulink url=\"&ecryptfs;\">eCryptfs</ulink>)"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19550
msgid "<ulink url=\"&dmcrypt;\">Dm-crypt</ulink> is a cryptographic filesystem using <ulink url=\"&devicemapper;\">device-mapper</ulink>. <ulink url=\"&devicemapper;\">Device-mapper</ulink> maps one block device to another."
msgstr "<ulink url=\"&dmcrypt;\">Dm-crypt</ulink> est un systme de fichiers chiffr qui utilise <ulink url=\"&devicemapper;\">device-mapper</ulink>. <ulink url=\"&devicemapper;\">Device-mapper</ulink> effectue le &nbsp;mapping&nbsp; d'un priphrique en mode bloc sur un autre."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19551
msgid "<ulink url=\"&ecryptfs;\">eCryptfs</ulink> is another cryptographic filesystem using stacked filesystem.  Stacked filesystem stacks itself on top of an existing directory of a mounted filesystem."
msgstr "<ulink url=\"&ecryptfs;\">eCryptfs</ulink> est un autre systme de fichiers chiffr utilisant un systme de fichier empilables.  Un systme de fichiers empilables s'empile lui-mme par dessus un rpertoire existant d'un systme de fichiers mont."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><caution><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19553
msgid "Data encryption costs CPU time etc.  Please weigh its benefits and costs."
msgstr "Le chiffrement des donnes a un cot en matire de temps CPU, etc. Veuillez comparer ses avantages  son cot."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><note><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19556
msgid "Entire Debian system can be installed on a encrypted disk by the <ulink url=\"&debianinstaller;\">debian-installer</ulink> (lenny or newer) using <ulink url=\"&dmcrypt;\">dm-crypt</ulink>/<ulink url=\"&luks;\">LUKS</ulink> and initramfs."
msgstr "Le systme Debian dans son ensemble peut tre install sur un disque chiffr par l'<ulink url=\"&debianinstaller;\">installateur debian</ulink> (lenny ou plus rcent) en utilisant <ulink url=\"&dmcrypt;\">dm-crypt</ulink>/<ulink url=\"&luks;\">LUKS</ulink> et initramfs."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19559
msgid "See <xref linkend=\"_data_security_infrastructure\"/> for user space encryption utility: <ulink url=\"&gnuprivacyguard;\">GNU Privacy Guard</ulink>."
msgstr "Voir <xref linkend=\"_data_security_infrastructure\"/> pour un utilitaire de chiffrement de l'espace utilisateur&nbsp;: <ulink url=\"&gnuprivacyguard;\">GNU Privacy Guard</ulink>."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19562
msgid "Removable disk encryption with dm-crypt/LUKS"
msgstr "Chiffrement des disques amovibles  l'aide de dm-crypt/LUKS"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19563
msgid "You can encrypt contents of removable mass devices, e.g. USB memory stick on \"<literal>/dev/sdx</literal>\", using <ulink url=\"&dmcrypt;\">dm-crypt</ulink>/<ulink url=\"&luks;\">LUKS</ulink>.  You simply formatting it as the following."
msgstr "Vous pouvez chiffrer le contenu des priphriques de masse amovible, par exemple, une cl g. USB memory stick sur &nbsp;<literal>/dev/sdx</literal>&nbsp; en utilisant <ulink url=\"&dmcrypt;\">dm-crypt</ulink>/<ulink url=\"&luks;\">LUKS</ulink>. Il suffit de le formater de la manire suivantes&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19564
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# badblocks -c 10240 -s -w -t random -v /dev/sdx\n"
"# shred -v -n 1 /dev/sdx\n"
"# fdisk /dev/sdx\n"
"... \"n\" \"p\" \"1\" \"return\" \"return\" \"w\"\n"
"# cryptsetup luksFormat /dev/sdx1\n"
"...\n"
"# cryptsetup luksOpen /dev/sdx1 sdx1\n"
"...\n"
"# ls -l /dev/mapper/\n"
"total 0\n"
"crw-rw---- 1 root root  10, 60 2008-10-04 18:44 control\n"
"brw-rw---- 1 root disk 254,  0 2008-10-04 23:55 sdx1\n"
"# mkfs.vfat /dev/mapper/sdx1\n"
"...\n"
"# cryptsetup luksClose sdx1"
msgstr ""
"# badblocks -c 10240 -s -w -t random -v /dev/sdx\n"
"# shred -v -n 1 /dev/sdx\n"
"# fdisk /dev/sdx\n"
"... \"n\" \"p\" \"1\" \"return\" \"return\" \"w\"\n"
"# cryptsetup luksFormat /dev/sdx1\n"
"...\n"
"# cryptsetup luksOpen /dev/sdx1 sdx1\n"
"...\n"
"# ls -l /dev/mapper/\n"
"total 0\n"
"crw-rw---- 1 root root  10, 60 2008-10-04 18:44 control\n"
"brw-rw---- 1 root disk 254,  0 2008-10-04 23:55 sdx1\n"
"# mkfs.vfat /dev/mapper/sdx1\n"
"...\n"
"# cryptsetup luksClose sdx1"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19579
msgid "Then, it can be mounted just like normal one on to \"<literal>/media/&lt;disk_label&gt;</literal>\", except for asking password (see <xref linkend=\"_removable_storage_device\"/>) under modern desktop environment, such as GNOME using <literal>gnome-mount</literal>(1).  The difference is that every data written to it is encrypted.  You may alternatively format media in different file format, e.g., ext3 with \"<literal>mkfs.ext3 /dev/sdx1</literal>\"."
msgstr "Il peut alors tre mont simplement comme un priphrique normal sur &nbsp;<literal>/media/&lt;disk_label&gt;</literal>&nbsp;  l'exception de la demande de mot de passe (voir <xref linkend=\"_removable_storage_device\"/>) sous un environnement de bureau moderne tel que GNOME en utilisant <literal>gnome-mount</literal>(1). La diffrence est que toutes les donnes qui y seront crites seront chiffres. Vous pouvez aussi formater le support dans un format diffrent, par exemple ext3 avec &nbsp;<literal>mkfs.ext3 /dev/sdx1</literal>&nbsp;."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><note><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19581
msgid "If you are really paranoid for the security of data, you may need to overwrite multiple times in the above example.  This operation is very time consuming though."
msgstr "Si vous tes vraiment paranoaque en ce qui concerne la scurit des donnes, vous pourrez rcrire par dessus plusieurs fois dans l'exemple ci-dessus. Cette opration est cependant trs exigeante en temps."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19585
msgid "Encrypted swap partition with dm-crypt"
msgstr "Partition d'change chiffre avec dm-crypt"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19586
msgid "Let's assume that your original \"<literal>/etc/fstab</literal>\" contains the following."
msgstr "Supposons que votre &nbsp;<literal>/etc/fstab</literal>&nbsp; d'origine comporte ce qui suit&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19587
#, no-wrap
msgid "/dev/sda7 swap sw 0 0"
msgstr "/dev/sda7 swap sw 0 0"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19588
msgid "You can enable encrypted swap partition using <ulink url=\"&dmcrypt;\">dm-crypt</ulink> by as the following."
msgstr "Vous pouvez chiffrer la partition d'change en utilisant <ulink url=\"&dmcrypt;\">dm-crypt</ulink> par ce qui suit&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19589
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# aptitude install cryptsetup\n"
"# swapoff -a\n"
"# echo \"cswap /dev/sda7 /dev/urandom swap\" &gt;&gt; /etc/crypttab\n"
"# perl -i -p -e \"s/\\/dev\\/sda7/\\/dev\\/mapper\\/cswap/\" /etc/fstab\n"
"# /etc/init.d/cryptdisks restart\n"
" ...\n"
"# swapon -a"
msgstr ""
"# aptitude install cryptsetup\n"
"# swapoff -a\n"
"# echo \"cswap /dev/sda7 /dev/urandom swap\" &gt;&gt; /etc/crypttab\n"
"# perl -i -p -e \"s/\\/dev\\/sda7/\\/dev\\/mapper\\/cswap/\" /etc/fstab\n"
"# /etc/init.d/cryptdisks restart\n"
" ...\n"
"# swapon -a"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19598
msgid "Automatically encrypting files with eCryptfs"
msgstr "Chiffrer les fichiers automatiquement avec eCryptfs"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19599
msgid "You can encrypt files written under \"<literal>~/Private/</literal>\" automatically using <ulink url=\"&ecryptfs;\">eCryptfs</ulink> and the <literal>ecryptfs-utils</literal> package."
msgstr "Vous pouvez chiffrer automatiquement les fichiers se trouvant sous &nbsp;<literal>~/Private/</literal>&nbsp; en utilisant <ulink url=\"&ecryptfs;\">eCryptfs</ulink> et le paquet <literal>ecryptfs-utils</literal>."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19603
msgid "Run <literal>ecryptfs-setup-private</literal>(1) and set up \"<literal>~/Private/</literal>\" by following prompts."
msgstr "Lancez <literal>ecryptfs-setup-private</literal>(1) et configurez &nbsp;<literal>~/Private/</literal>&nbsp; en suivant les invites."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19608
msgid "Activate \"<literal>~/Private/</literal>\" by running <literal>ecryptfs-mount-private</literal>(1)."
msgstr "Activez &nbsp;<literal>~/Private/</literal>&nbsp; en lanant <literal>ecryptfs-mount-private</literal>(1)."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19613
msgid "Move sensitive data files to \"<literal>~/Private/</literal>\" and make symlinks as needed."
msgstr "Dplacez les fichiers de donnes sensibles vers &nbsp;<literal>~/Private/</literal>&nbsp; et faites les liens symboliques  la demande."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19618
msgid "Candidates: \"<literal>~/.fetchmailrc</literal>\", \"<literal>~/.ssh/identity</literal>\", \"<literal>~/.ssh/id_rsa</literal>\", \"<literal>~/.ssh/id_dsa</literal>\" and other files with \"<literal>go-rwx</literal>\""
msgstr "Candidats&nbsp;: &nbsp;<literal>~/.fetchmailrc</literal>&nbsp;, &nbsp;<literal>~/.ssh/identity</literal>&nbsp;, &nbsp;<literal>~/.ssh/id_rsa</literal>&nbsp;, &nbsp;<literal>~/.ssh/id_dsa</literal>&nbsp; et d'autres fichiers ayant &nbsp;<literal>go-rwx</literal>&nbsp;"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19625
msgid "Move sensitive data directories to a subdirectory in \"<literal>~/Private/</literal>\" and make symlinks as needed."
msgstr "Dplacez les rpertoires ayant des donnes sensibles vers un sous-rpertoire de &nbsp;<literal>~/Private/</literal>&nbsp; et faites les liens symboliques ncessaires."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19630
msgid "Candidates: \"<literal>~/.gnupg</literal>\" and other directories with \"<literal>go-rwx</literal>\""
msgstr "Candidats&nbsp;: &nbsp;<literal>~/.gnupg</literal>&nbsp; et d'autres rpertoires avec &nbsp;<literal>go-rwx</literal>&nbsp;"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19637
msgid "Create symlink from \"<literal>~/Desktop/Private/</literal>\" to \"<literal>~/Private/</literal>\" for easier desktop operations."
msgstr "Crez le lien symbolique de &nbsp;<literal>~/Desktop/Private/</literal>&nbsp; vers &nbsp;<literal>~/Private/</literal>&nbsp; pour faciliter les oprations du bureau."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19642
msgid "Deactivate \"<literal>~/Private/</literal>\" by running <literal>ecryptfs-umount-private</literal>(1)."
msgstr "Dsactiver &nbsp;<literal>~/Private/</literal>&nbsp; en lanant <literal>ecryptfs-umount-private</literal>(1)."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19647
msgid "Activate \"<literal>~/Private/</literal>\" by issuing \"<literal>ecryptfs-mount-private</literal>\" as you need encrypted data."
msgstr "Activez &nbsp;<literal>~/Private/</literal>&nbsp;  l'aide de &nbsp;<literal>ecryptfs-mount-private</literal>&nbsp; lorsque vous avez besoin de vos donnes chiffres."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19652
msgid "Since <ulink url=\"&ecryptfs;\">eCryptfs</ulink> selectively encrypt only the sensitive files, its system cost is much less than using <ulink url=\"&dmcrypt;\">dm-crypt</ulink> on the entire root or \"<literal>/home</literal>\" device.  It does not require any special on-disk storage allocation effort but cannot keep all filesystem metadata confidential."
msgstr "Comme <ulink url=\"&ecryptfs;\">eCryptfs</ulink> ne chiffre que slectivement les fichiers sensibles, son cot en matire de ressources systme est bien moindre que l'utilisation de <ulink url=\"&dmcrypt;\">dm-crypt</ulink> sur l'ensemble du systme de  fichiers racine ou sur le priphrique &nbsp;<literal>/home</literal>&nbsp;. Il ne demande aucun effort  particulier sur l'allocation de l'espace disque mais ne peut conserver la confidentialit de toutes les mta-donnes du systme de fichiers."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19656
msgid "Automatically mounting eCryptfs"
msgstr "Montage automatique de eCryptfs"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19657
msgid "If you use your login password for wrapping encryption keys, you can automate mounting eCryptfs via <ulink url=\"&pampluggableauthnticationmodules;\">PAM (Pluggable Authentication Modules)</ulink>."
msgstr "Si vous utilisez votre mot de passe de connexion pour envelopper les cls de chiffrement, vous pouvez automatiser le montage de eCryptfs par <ulink url=\"&pampluggableauthnticationmodules;\">PAM (Pluggable Authentication Modules)</ulink>."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19659
msgid "Insert the following line just before \"<literal>pam_permit.so</literal>\" in \"<literal>/etc/pam.d/common-auth</literal>\"."
msgstr "Insrez la ligne suivante juste avant &nbsp;<literal>pam_permit.so</literal>&nbsp; dans &nbsp;<literal>/etc/pam.d/common-auth</literal>&nbsp;&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19660
#, no-wrap
msgid "auth required pam_ecryptfs.so unwrap"
msgstr "auth required pam_ecryptfs.so unwrap"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19661
msgid "Insert the following line just at the last line in \"<literal>/etc/pam.d/common-session</literal>\"."
msgstr "Insrez la ligne suivante en tant que toute dernire ligne de &nbsp;<literal>/etc/pam.d/common-session</literal>&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19662
#, no-wrap
msgid "session optional pam_ecryptfs.so unwrap"
msgstr "session optional pam_ecryptfs.so unwrap"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19663
msgid "Insert the following line at first active line in \"<literal>/etc/pam.d/common-password</literal>\"."
msgstr "Insrez la ligne suivante comme premire ligne active de &nbsp;<literal>/etc/pam.d/common-password</literal>&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19664
#, no-wrap
msgid "password required pam_ecryptfs.so"
msgstr "password required pam_ecryptfs.so"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19665
msgid "This is quite convenient."
msgstr "C'est assez pratique."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19667
msgid "Configuration errors of <ulink url=\"&pam;\">PAM</ulink> may lock you out of your own system. See <xref linkend=\"_authentication\"/>."
msgstr "Les erreurs de configuration de <ulink url=\"&pam;\">PAM</ulink> peuvent vous interdire l'accs  votre propre systme. Voir <xref linkend=\"_authentication\"/>."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><caution><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19670
msgid "If you use your login password for wrapping encryption keys, your encrypted data are as secure as your user login password (see <xref linkend=\"_good_password\"/>).  Unless you are careful to set up a <ulink url=\"&strongpassword;\">strong password</ulink>, your data is at risk when someone runs <ulink url=\"&passwordcracking;\">password cracking</ulink> software after stealing your laptop (see <xref linkend=\"_securing_the_root_password\"/>)."
