#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30012
msgid "Debug is important part of programing activities.  Knowing how to debug programs makes you a good Debian user who can produce meaningful bug reports."
msgstr "Le dbogage est une partie de l'activit de programmations. Savoir comme dboguer des programmes fera de vous un bon utilisateur de Debian qui pourra produire des rapports de bogues documents."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30014
msgid "Basic gdb execution"
msgstr "Excution de base de gdb"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30015
msgid "Primary <ulink url=\"&debugger;\">debugger</ulink> on Debian is <literal>gdb</literal>(1) which enables you to inspect a program while it executes."
msgstr "Le <ulink url=\"&debugger;\">debogueur</ulink> primaire sous Debian est <literal>gdb</literal>(1), il vous permet d'inspecter un programme alors qu'il tourne."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30016
msgid "Let's install <literal>gdb</literal> and related programs by the following."
msgstr "Installons <literal>gdb</literal> et les programmes associs par ce qui  suit&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30017
#, no-wrap
msgid "# aptitude install gdb gdb-doc build-essential devscripts"
msgstr "# aptitude install gdb gdb-doc build-essential devscripts"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30018
msgid "Good tutorial of <literal>gdb</literal> is provided by \"<literal>info gdb</literal>\" or found <ulink url=\"&elsewhereontheweb;\">elsewhere on the web</ulink>.  Here is a simple example of using <literal>gdb</literal>(1) on a \"<literal>program</literal>\" compiled with the \"<literal>-g</literal>\" option to produce debugging information."
msgstr "Un bon didacticiel de <literal>gdb</literal> est propos par &nbsp;<literal>info gdb</literal>&nbsp; ou peut tre trouv <ulink url=\"&elsewhereontheweb;\">ailleurs sur le web</ulink>. Voici un exemple simple d'utilisation de <literal>gdb</literal>(1) sur un &nbsp;<literal>program</literal>&nbsp; compil avec l'option &nbsp;<literal>-g</literal>&nbsp; qui produit les informations de dbogage."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30020
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ gdb program\n"
"(gdb) b 1                # set break point at line 1\n"
"(gdb) run args           # run program with args\n"
"(gdb) next               # next line\n"
"...\n"
"(gdb) step               # step forward\n"
"...\n"
"(gdb) p parm             # print parm\n"
"...\n"
"(gdb) p parm=12          # set value to 12\n"
"...\n"
"(gdb) quit"
msgstr ""
"$ gdb program\n"
"(gdb) b 1                # dfinit un point d'arrt  la ligne 1\n"
"(gdb) run args           # lancer les programmes avec des paramtres \n"
"(gdb) next               # ligne suivante\n"
"...\n"
"(gdb) step               # avancer d'un pas\n"
"...\n"
"(gdb) p parm             # afficher parm\n"
"...\n"
"(gdb) p parm=12          # dfinir sa valeur  12\n"
"...\n"
"(gdb) quit"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30033
msgid "Many <literal>gdb</literal>(1) commands can be abbreviated.  Tab expansion works as in the shell."
msgstr "De nombreuses commandes de <literal>gdb</literal>(1) possdent une abrviation. L'expansion  l'aide de la touche de tabulation fonctionne comme avec l'interprteur de commandes."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30037
msgid "Debugging the Debian package"
msgstr "Dboguer un paquet Debian"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30038
msgid "Since all installed binaries should be stripped on the Debian system by default, most debugging symbols are removed in the normal package.  In order to debug Debian packages with <literal>gdb</literal>(1), corresponding <literal>*-dbg</literal> packages need to be installed (e.g. <literal>libc6-dbg</literal> in the case of <literal>libc6</literal>)."
msgstr "Comme, par dfaut, sous Debian, tous les paquets binaires sont &nbsp;stripps&nbsp; (dpouills de leurs symboles de dbogage), la plupart des symboles de dbogage sont supprims des paquets normaux. Pour pouvoir dboguer des paquets Debian  l'aide de <literal>gdb</literal>(1), les paquets <literal>*-dbg</literal> correspondants doivent tre installs (par exemple <literal>libc6-dbg</literal> dans le cas de <literal>libc6</literal>)."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30039
msgid "If a package to be debugged does not provide its <literal>*-dbg</literal> package, you need to install it after rebuilding it by the following."
msgstr "Si un paquet  dboguer ne possde pas de paquet <literal>*-dbg</literal> correspondant, vous devrez l'installer aprs l'avoir reconstruit comme suit&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30040
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ mkdir /path/new ; cd /path/new\n"
"$ sudo aptitude update\n"
"$ sudo aptitude dist-upgrade\n"
"$ sudo aptitude install fakeroot devscripts build-essential\n"
"$ sudo apt-get build-dep source_package_name\n"
"$ apt-get source package_name\n"
"$ cd package_name*"
msgstr ""
"$ mkdir /chemin/nouveau ; cd /chemin/nouveau\n"
"$ sudo aptitude update\n"
"$ sudo aptitude dist-upgrade\n"
"$ sudo aptitude install fakeroot devscripts build-essential\n"
"$ sudo apt-get build-dep nom_paquet_source\n"
"$ apt-get nom_paquet_source\n"
"$ cd nom_paquet*"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30047
msgid "Fix bugs if needed."
msgstr "Corriger les bogues si ncessaire."

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30048
msgid "Bump package version to one which does not collide with official Debian versions, e.g. one appended with \"<literal>+debug1</literal>\" when recompiling existing package version, or one appended with \"<literal>~pre1</literal>\" when compiling unreleased package version by the following."
msgstr "Modifier la version du paquet pour ne pas entrer en collision avec les versions officielles de Debian, par exemple, en ajoutant &nbsp;<literal>+debug1</literal>&nbsp; pour la compilation d'une version de paquet existante, ou &nbsp;<literal>~pre1</literal>&nbsp; pour la compilation d'une version de paquet qui n'est pas encore diffuse de la manire suivante&nbsp;:"

#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30050
msgid "Compile and install packages with debug symbols by the following."
msgstr "Compiler et installer les  paquets avec les symboles de dbogage comme suit&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30051
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ export DEB_BUILD_OPTIONS=nostrip,noopt\n"
"$ debuild\n"
"$ cd ..\n"
"$ sudo debi package_name*.changes"
msgstr ""
"$ export DEB_BUILD_OPTIONS=nostrip,noopt\n"
"$ debuild\n"
